reviews.review_text:
Even better than the night before... Ecstatic, triumphant Terrapin -- the tiny missing bit in segue to mystic drums is virtually OK, I wouldn't have even noticed it but for liner notes, and it for sure isn't anything to fret over.

The Dead own Watchtower tonight.

Recommend you listen to last night first, then tonight.

A whole new spin on Ashes, Ashes: I recently learned that the Ring Around The Rosies children's game came about during the Bubonic Plague, with "ring around the rosies" referring to the ringed, rosy cheeks (like marker for Lyme's Disease) of the recently afflicted and doomed; "pocket full of posies" referring to nosegays of flowers & herbs to ward off infection, with refreshers on the ready in one's pocket;  and, "ashes, ashes, we all fall down!" referring to death, cremation, and the resulting ashes in the wind [immolation was believed to help contain the spread]. So there you have it, if it works for you.
